{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UTF8View","kind":"identifier"}],"extendedModule":"Swift","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UTF8View","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"externalID":"s:SS8UTF8ViewV","title":"String.UTF8View"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Related String Types","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Substring","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/StringProtocol","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/Index","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/CharacterView","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UnicodeScalarView","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UTF16View","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/Iterator","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/Output"],"anchor":"Related-String-Types"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@frozen"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UTF8View"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can access a string’s view of UTF-8 code units by using its "},{"code":"utf8","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property. A string’s UTF-8 view encodes the string’s Unicode scalar"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values as 8-bit integers."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let flowers = \"Flowers 💐\"","for v in flowers.utf8 {","    print(v)","}","// 70","// 108","// 111","// 119","// 101","// 114","// 115","// 32","// 240","// 159","// 146","// 144"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A string’s Unicode scalar values can be up to 21 bits in length. To"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"represent those scalar values using 8-bit integers, more than one UTF-8"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"code unit is often required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let flowermoji = \"💐\"","for v in flowermoji.unicodeScalars {","    print(v, v.value)","}","// 💐 128144","","for v in flowermoji.utf8 {","    print(v)","}","// 240","// 159","// 146","// 144"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the encoded representation of a Unicode scalar value, each UTF-8 code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unit after the first is called a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"continuation byte"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":1,"type":"heading","text":"UTF8View Elements Match Encoded C Strings","anchor":"UTF8View-Elements-Match-Encoded-C-Strings"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift streamlines interoperation with C string APIs by letting you pass a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" instance to a function as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int8"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"UInt8","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" pointer. When you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call a C function using a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":", Swift automatically creates a buffer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of UTF-8 code units and passes a pointer to that buffer. The code units"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of that buffer match the code units in the string’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"utf8","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" view.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses the C "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strncmp"},{"type":"text","text":" function to compare the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"beginning of two Swift strings. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strncmp"},{"type":"text","text":" function takes two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"const char*"},{"type":"text","text":" pointers and an integer specifying the number of characters"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to compare. Because the strings are identical up to the 14th character,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"comparing only those characters results in a return value of "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let s1 = \"They call me 'Bell'\"","let s2 = \"They call me 'Stacey'\"","","print(strncmp(s1, s2, 14))","// Prints \"0\"","print(String(s1.utf8.prefix(14))!)","// Prints \"They call me '\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Extending the compared character count to 15 includes the differing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"characters, so a nonzero result is returned."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["print(strncmp(s1, s2, 15))","// Prints \"-17\"","print(String(s1.utf8.prefix(15))!)","// Prints \"They call me 'B\""]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/BidirectionalCollection","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Collection","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Copyable","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomDebugStringConvertible","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomReflectable","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomStringConvertible","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Escapable","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/S